<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">All Students, Faculty and Staff</span></h1>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">It is with heavy hearts and deep regret that the Board of Regents announces that after 95 years of fulfilling the dream of Dr. Rosa J. Young, Concordia Alabama (CCA) will close its doors at the end of the spring semester 2018.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">No new students will be admitted after the current semester.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">Current students will be assisted with their personal higher education goals. Faculty and staff will be assisted in finding new positions. CCA is in the process of developing a Teach-Out Plan which will be submitted to the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges (SACSCOC), for its approval. We will also inform other appropriate state and federal agencies.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">We appreciate the many private individuals, alumni, and friends of the college who have helped sustain it over these many years.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">“The Board of Regents” deeply appreciates the work of the faculty, staff, and others who have worked tirelessly, and at personal sacrifice, to keep Concordia College Alabama viable. We wish them the Lord’s Blessings as they move to other positions” said Mr. Lloyd Probasco, chairman of the Board of Regents.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong><u>Transcript Requests</u></strong> will be processed at Concordia through September 28, 2018. Please do not call Concordia College Alabama after this date; no one will be available to take your call.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">In the event of an emergency prior to Oct. 15th, former students seeking their transcripts should send an email to one of the following:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">cwashington@ccal.edu</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">bethubbard@ccal.edu</span></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;"><em><strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong></em><strong><em><br />

</em></strong><em><strong>Mr. Ed Siffring, University Registrar: </strong></em><strong><em>registrar@cune.edu</em></strong><em><strong>, <a style="color: #ffffff;" href="callto:402-643-7230">402-643-7230</a></strong></em></span></p>
